canonical:
  title: 賀節日表
  author: 李達衷
  language: lzh
  text: 四月維夏欣逢誕聖之辰諸侯來朝共獻齊天之壽廷儀肅肅福物穰穰云云受命于天視民如子恩均普率推離明而照四方德務寬仁以比▣而親萬國爰値虹流之旦競祈川至之休况小邦蒙賴實多故今日賀悰彌篤云云邈乎守土無以瞻天穆穆耿光何敢忘於造次區區丹懇但常祝於康寧
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀節日表
  author: 李達衷
  language: lzh
  text: 四月維夏。欣逢誕聖之辰。諸侯來朝。共獻齊天之壽。廷儀肅肅。福物穰穰。云云。受命于天。視民如子。恩均普率。推離明而照四方。德務寬仁。以比▣而親萬國爰値虹流之旦。競祈川至之休。况小邦蒙賴實多。故今日賀悰彌篤。云云。邈乎守土。無以瞻天。穆穆耿光。何敢忘於造次。區區丹懇。但常祝於康寧。
korean:
  title: 하 절일 표
  author: 이달충
  language: kor
  text: 4월이라 여름철에 탄성(誕聖)의 가절(佳節)을 반가이 만나, 제후(諸侯)들이 내조(來朝)하여 함께 하늘과 똑같으실 수(壽)를 올리오니, 조정의 의식이 숙숙(肅肅)하고 복된 공물(貢物)이 양양(穰穰)하도소이다. 운운. 명(命)을 하늘에서 받으시와 백성을 아들처럼 보시니, 은혜가 지상(地上)에 고름[均]은 이괘(离卦)의 밝음을 밀어 사방을 비춤이요, 덕이 관인(寬仁)을 힘쓰심은 비괘(比卦)□으로써 만국을 친하심이로소이다. 이제 ‘무재개가 흐른 날’을 만나 다투어 ‘냇물이 흘러오는 것’과 같은 복을 비옵는데 하물며 소방(小邦)은 은혜를 입사옴이 실로 많으므로, 오늘 축하하옵는 정성이 더욱 돈독(敦篤)하옵나이다. 운운. 머나먼 곳에 땅을 지키는 몸이라서 하늘을 바라볼 수 없사오나, 목목(穆穆)하신 경광(耿光)을 어찌 잠깐인들 잊사오리이까. 구구한 단심(丹心)으로 다만 항상 강녕(康寧)을 축원하옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0250&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Memorial Offering Felicitations on the Festival Day
  author: Lee Dal-choong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    In the fourth month of summer, we joyfully greet this auspicious day of the royal birth. The lords of ten thousand realms come to court and together offer tribute as vast as the heavens themselves. The ceremonies of the palace stand solemn and dignified; the offerings of blessing flow in abundance.

    Your Majesty receives the mandate from Heaven and views the people as your own children. Your grace spreads equally across all lands, its brilliance radiating like the sun to illuminate the four directions. Your virtue earnestly pursues benevolence and kinship, drawing all nations near as if through the power of harmony. On this day when the rainbow appears after rain, all compete to invoke blessings as numerous as flowing streams. How much more so for our small realm, whose debt of gratitude is truly immense. Thus does our felicitation today burn all the more ardently in our hearts.

    Though we stand far away, guarding these distant lands and unworthy to gaze upon the heavens, how could we ever forget—even for a moment—your serene and radiant virtue? With this sincere and devoted heart, we offer constant prayers for your eternal peace and prosperity.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'fourth month' refers to the lunar calendar. The phrase 'as vast as the heavens' alludes to birthday wishes matching the span of heaven itself.
  - key: ''
    value: 'The references to the I Ching hexagrams (離卦 Li and 比卦 Bi) invoke Confucian symbolism: Li represents illumination and the south, while Bi represents harmony and alliance.'
  - key: ''
    value: The 'rainbow appearing after rain' is a traditional auspicious omen in East Asian poetry, symbolizing divine favor and blessing.
  - key: ''
    value: This is a formal diplomatic memorial in praise of a ruler's birthday or coronation, likely written during Joseon dynasty period when Korean kingdoms maintained tributary relations with China.
